p page of the reservation; 1 adult traveling with 1 child, the child must occupy the bed, please select Children occupy the bed and make up the difference.</p></td></tr><tr><th>Supplement</th><td><p>Customs taxation of entry and exit personal belongings; shipping and storage fees for excess luggage; personal consumption such as laundry, haircut, telephone, fax, pay TV, drinks, tobacco and alcohol in the hotel; car service during free activities; providing tour guide services The product does not have accompanying services during the free activities; local participation at their own expense and other items not included in the cost included</p><p>Single room supplement</p></td></tr></tbody></table></div></dd></dl><dl class=\"mod_info_box\"><dt>Recommended activities reference (at your own expense)</dt><dd><div class=\"tour_self_table_box\"><table class=\"tour_self_table\"><tbody><tr><th style=\"width: 170px;\">Activity</th><th style=\"width: 110px;\">Proposed Price</th><th>Description</th></tr><tr><td>Philae Temple Sound and Light Show</td><td>70 USD/person (2-5 people)</td><td>70 USD/person (2-5 people) 65 USD/person (6-9 people) 60 USD/person (10 people and above) The expenses include: fare, tour guide fee, attraction ticket</td></tr><tr><td>Pyramid Sound and Light Show</td><td>75 USD/person (2-5 people)</td><td>Under the combination of modern sound and light, experience the vicissitudes of history more than 4,000 years ago. Includes pick-up service, Chinese-speaking tour guide and tickets.<br>75 USD/person (2-5 people)<br>65 USD/person (over 6 people)<br></td></tr><tr><td>Night Cruise on the Nile</td><td>85 USD/person (4-9 people)</td><td>In the evening, take a cruise on the Nile River to enjoy the scenery on both sides of the river, and have dinner on the boat (without drinks) and enjoy local special performances (the performance will be suspended during Ramadan). Includes pick-up and drop-off service from the pier, as well as Chinese-speaking tour guide escort service<br>85 USD/person (4-9 people)<br> 75 USD/person (10 people and above)<br></td></tr><tr><td>Abu Simbel Temple</td><td>145 USD/person</td><td>Depart at about 4 in the morning and go and return under the desert guard. The Temple of Abu Simbel is the focus of tourism in Aswan. It was built by the great pharaoh Ramses II of ancient Egypt, and is also a protected relic during the Pharaoh era of the new empire. Including fare, Chinese-speaking tour guide escort and explanation service, and attraction tickets<br>145 USD / person (6-9 people)<br>140 USD/person (10-14 people)<br>125 USD/person (15 people and above)<br></td></tr><tr><td>Aswan Nubian Village Tour</td><td>50 USD/person (4-7 people)</td><td>Take a boat to Aswan's unique ethnic minority village-Nubian Village. Here you can experience the ancient Nubian civilization, visit the colorful houses unique to the Nubians, learn the local language, and visit the home. Includes pick-up and drop-off service from the pier, accompanied by a Chinese-speaking guide, as well as Nubian village specialty drinks and camel riding.<br>50 USD/person (4-7 people)<br>45 USD/person (8 people and above)<br></td></tr><tr><td>Four-wheel Drive Jeep Rushing</td><td>90 USD/person (4-7 people)</td><td>Around 2:30 in the afternoon, take a four-wheel drive from the hotel and head to the desert next door to the eastern part of Egypt for sand washing. Free yourself in the empty next door. Climb to the top of the dunes to enjoy the sunset. Afterwards, head to the ancient Bedouin village to explore the life of the Bedouin. And experience the fun of riding a camel. If you are lucky on the way back, you can see the sky full of stars.<br>Note: This item is an irritating item. The driving process of 4WD vehicles is quite bumpy and there is a certain risk. Please take part carefully! Please pay attention to safety when getting on and off the camel! If the car seat is not equipped with a seat belt, please refuse to board the car and request a refund of the corresponding fee!<br>90 USD/person (4-7 people)<br>80 USD/person (more than 8 people)<br>The expenses include: 4*4 jeep fare, tour guide fee, attraction ticket, BBQ dinner</td></tr><tr><td>Giftun Island Tour</td><td>80 USD/person (over 10 people)</td><td>Depart from the hotel at around 8:30 in the morning, head to the pier, board the yacht, and enter the beautiful Red Sea. Chartered boats do not join other tourists to enjoy the scenery of the Red Sea. Feeding seagulls, fishing, snorkeling and various amusement options. Snorkeling equipment and basic fishing equipment are provided on the yacht. Enjoy a simple lunch on the boat at noon. Including pick-up and drop-off service, accompanied by a Chinese-speaking guide.<br>Note:<br>Please pay attention to safety when you disembark from the sea on a yacht. Do not queue up and slide carefully. The captain and lifeguard should not make dangerous actions before making arrangements. As the yacht is fast and the sea is more bumpy, the elderly, weak, women, children and patients please participate carefully! )<br>80 USD/person (over 10 people)<br></td></tr><tr><td>Sinbad Submarine</td><td>115 USD/person (from 2 people)</td><td>Go to the pier and take a speedboat to the submarine platform. Take a submarine to dive into the 7-meter deep Red Sea and enjoy the mysterious and beautiful underwater world of the Red Sea. And some divers will give you a performance of feeding fish under the sea. Including pick-up and drop-off, accompanied by a Chinese guide<br>Note:<br>This program is an irritating. Due to certain pressure under the sea, for the elderly, weak, women, children and patients please participate carefully!<br>115 USD/person (from 2 people)</td></tr><tr><td>Red Sea Glass Boat Tour</td><td>70 USD/person (from 4 people)</td><td>Take a specially customized cruise ship with large sightseeing windows at the bottom of the cruise ship, which is convenient for enjoying the wonderful underwater world. Includes pick-up and drop-o