ve)<br></td></tr><tr><td>Abu Simbel Temple</td><td>145 USD/person</td><td>Depart at about 4 in the morning and go and return under the desert guard. The Temple of Abu Simbel is the focus of tourism in Aswan. It was built by the great pharaoh Ramses II of ancient Egypt, and is also a protected relic during the Pharaoh era of the new empire. Including fare, Chinese-speaking tour guide escort and explanation service, and attraction tickets<br>145 USD / person (6-9 people)<br>140 USD/person (10-14 people)<br>125 USD/person (15 people and above)<br></td></tr><tr><td>Aswan Nubian Village Tour</td><td>50 USD/person (4-7 people)</td><td>Take a boat to Aswan's unique ethnic minority village-Nubian Village. Here you can experience the ancient Nubian civilization, visit the colorful houses unique to the Nubians, learn the local language, and visit the home. Includes pick-up and drop-off service from the pier, accompanied by a Chinese-speaking guide, as well as Nubian village specialty drinks and camel riding.<br>50 USD/person (4-7 people)<br>45 USD/person (8 people and above)<br></td></tr><tr><td>Four-wheel Drive Jeep Rushing</td><td>90 USD/person (4-7 people)</td><td>Around 2:30 in the afternoon, take a four-wheel drive from the hotel and head to the desert next door to the eastern part of Egypt for sand washing. Free yourself in the empty next door. Climb to the top of the dunes to enjoy the sunset. Afterwards, head to the ancient Bedouin village to explore the life of the Bedouin. And experience the fun of riding a camel. If you are lucky on the way back, you can see the sky full of stars.<br>Note: This item is an irritating item. The driving process of 4WD vehicles is quite bumpy and there is a certain risk. Please take part carefully! Please pay attention to safety when getting on and off the camel! If the car seat is not equipped with a seat belt, please refuse to board the car and request a refund of the corresponding fee!<br>90 USD/person (4-7 people)<br>80 USD/person 